The President has signed H.R. 3236, the "Surface Transportation and Veterans Health Care Choice Improvement Act of 2015." This law extends the authority and funding for the Department of Transportation's surface transportation programs until October 29, 2015. It also transfers $8.1 billion from the Treasury General Fund to the Highway Trust Fund. Additionally, the law provides resource flexibility to the Department of Veterans Affairs for health care services and makes changes to the Veterans Access, Choice and Accountability Act.